Coding for Conditional Coloring of the plots 7


How to Create and use your own measures


With Power BI Desktop, you can create your own measures with the Data Analysis Expressions (DAX) formula language, any field that appears with a sigma icon  is numeric, and its values can be aggregated, Sum is the default aggregation for a numeric datatype, but you can easily apply different aggregations like average or count. 


Note:  Actual measure for the code for the Color Saturation: 

ColorKPI = Switch ( TRUE(),
AND(SUM(sales[Profit Margin % ]) < 20 , SUM(Sales[Total Discount % ]) < 0.5), "#b20000",

AND(SUM(Sales[Profit Margin % ]) <=30, SUM(Sales[Total Discount % ]) <= 1), "#ffc04c", "#008000")


Note: The above measure has been uploaded for your convenience. Download from the above button.

Steps:

  1. Click new measure from Home menu.
  2. write the DAX code written above to the measurement created.




Steps 2:

1.  Click the Scatter plot chart in the dashboard - > select the format tab.

2.  Select Data color and Click Conditional formatting (another version "Advanced control).

3. Click Format by a tab.

4. Select "Field Value" from the format by Drill down menu.

5. Click Based on field drill down the tab and select ColorKPI column from the menu -> Click OK.

Finally, the color of the bubbles changed to explain the KPI.

  • Green color - tells highest KPI (profit margin and Total discount percentage)
  • Yellow color - tells average KPI value.
  • Red color - tells the lowest KPI value.
